---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ArticleSchema from '../../components/ArticleSchema.astro';
import TldrBox from '../../components/TldrBox.astro';
import FaqSection from '../../components/FaqSection.astro';
import ToolReview from '../../components/ToolReview.astro';
import { site, description, pageTitle } from '../../content';
import { useCaseBySlug } from '../../data/use-cases';
import { appBySlug } from '../../data/apps';

const uc = useCaseBySlug('holiday-gifting')!;
const path = '/use-cases/holiday-gifting';
const title = pageTitle(site, 'use-cases/holiday-gifting');
const desc = description(site, 'use-cases/holiday-gifting');

const featuredSlugs = ['sequenzy', 'klaviyo', 'omnisend', 'privy', 'yotpo-email-sms'];
const featuredApps = featuredSlugs.map((s) => appBySlug(s)!).filter(Boolean);

const comparisonApps = [
  'sequenzy', 'klaviyo', 'omnisend', 'privy', 'yotpo-email-sms', 'drip',
  'shopify-email', 'postscript', 'mailchimp', 'aftership-email',
].map((s) => appBySlug(s)!).filter(Boolean);

const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'What Shopify email tool handles holiday gifting campaigns best?',
    answer: 'Sequenzy ranks first for gift branching playbooks — gift buyer versus self-purchase, shipping deadline urgency, gift card last-minute escape hatch. Klaviyo wins at scale with market-specific cutoff segments and gift guide dynamic content. AfterShip pairing helps when delivery timing drives gift messaging.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How should gift buyers differ from self-purchasers in email?',
    answer: 'Gift buyers get gift guide, bundle ideas, shipping deadline reminders, gift message options — not replenishment or usage education for products they will not use. Pottery gift mug buyer should not receive glaze care for daily use — recipient might, if email captured.',
  },
  {
    question: 'When should shipping deadline emails send?',
    answer: 'Escalate by market — domestic standard minus 7 days, 3 days, 1 day; express cutoff separate email. Vinyl and board games need carrier-specific dates in dynamic blocks. After cutoff: pivot to digital gift card and printable gift note, not false ship promises.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Should holiday gift emails include discounts?',
    answer: 'Gift bundles and free gift wrap yes; blanket deeper discount on entire catalog trains waiting. VIP gift buyers get early gift guide access full-price; sensitive segment gets bundled value without stacking on BFCM if overlap. See discount strategy guide.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How do gift guides work in newsletter versus lifecycle?',
    answer: 'Newsletter gift guide edition four weeks out — editorial, curated bundles, pottery sets, tea samplers, vinyl starter packs. Lifecycle triggers on gift-intent browse or gift wrap SKU purchase — deadline series automatically. Same products, different send logic.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What post-purchase email do gift orders need?',
    answer: 'Thank-you to gifter, optional "treat yourself" soft pitch at day 21, no replenishment on consumables gifted. Separate recipient welcome if email available — climbing chalk gift kit care goes to recipient. Transactional shipping to gifter with gift-appropriate messaging.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How do gift card last-minute emails work?',
    answer: 'Trigger December 18–23 for segments who browsed gift guide but did not purchase — digital delivery instant, printable PDF option. Climbing gear and outdoor retailers recover 8–12% of late gift intent via gift card email in merchant tests.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Can Shopify Email run gift deadline automation?',
    answer: 'Shopify Email handles one-off gift announcements, not behavioral gift-intent branching, market-specific cutoff automation, or gift-versus-self post-purchase splits. Holiday gifting at revenue scale needs lifecycle platform.',
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={desc} site={site} path={path}>
  <ArticleSchema title={title} description={desc} siteName={site.name} domain={site.domain} path={path} />

  <section class="relative overflow-hidden py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/use-cases" class="text-sm font-bold text-[#9a5b16] hover:text-[#24170f]">← All use cases</a>
      <p class="catalog-kicker mt-6">Holiday gifting</p>
      <h1 class="hero-title mt-5 max-w-5xl">Best Shopify email tools for holiday gifting</h1>
      <p class="mt-7 max-w-3xl text-xl leading-9 text-[#4a2d17]">
        Holiday gifting email is a logistics and audience narrative — shipping cutoffs, gift bundles, gift card escape hatches, and gift-buyer post-purchase that does not assume the buyer is the recipient. A pottery studio emailing mug care instructions to December gift purchasers wastes sends; a vinyl shop pushing personal collection recommendations to someone buying a gift subscription confuses both parties. The right Shopify email tool branches on gift order signals, escalates deadline urgency by market, and pivots to digital gifts when carriers close the window.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-5 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-8 text-[#5d3a1d]">
        This playbook ranks email tools for {uc.job}. We evaluated gift detection, deadline automation, gift guide newsletters, and post-gift lifecycle — not generic "holiday sale" templates with snowflake backgrounds. December revenue from gifters requires different copy, timing, and post-purchase logic than self-purchase holiday shopping — conflating the two is how pottery studios email mug care to people who bought gifts for mothers-in-law.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-9 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/apps">Full tool catalog</a>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/use-cases/black-friday">Black Friday</a>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/use-cases/post-purchase">Post-purchase</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container pb-12">
    <TldrBox
      title="Top Shopify email tools for holiday gifting"
      picks={[
        { label: 'Best overall', tool: 'Sequenzy', reason: 'Gift branching playbooks with deadline escalation, gift card pivot, and gifter versus recipient post-purchase paths.' },
        { label: 'Best data depth', tool: 'Klaviyo', reason: 'Market-specific cutoff segments, gift guide dynamic content, and gift-intent behavioral triggers.' },
        { label: 'Best multichannel', tool: 'Omnisend', reason: 'Email plus SMS shipping deadline reminders with shared gift segment suppression.' },
        { label: 'Best gift capture', tool: 'Privy', reason: 'Gift guide lead capture and gift-intent popup metadata for downstream branching.' },
        { label: 'Best social proof', tool: 'Yotpo Email & SMS', reason: 'Gift-appropriate review highlights in gift guide emails when social proof closes gift buyer anxiety.' },
      ]}
    />

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Three holiday gifting merchant scenarios</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Scenario A — Pottery studio, 40% December gift orders.</strong> Sequenzy gift branch: gifter post-purchase thank-you plus optional self-purchase pitch day 21; recipient care email if address captured. Shipping deadline series domestic minus 7, 3, 1 day. Gift card pivot December 20 recovered 9% of late intent. Replenishment suppressed for gifters on consumable-adjacent gift sets.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Scenario B — Vinyl label, gift subscription and LP bundles.</strong> Klaviyo gift guide newsletter four weeks out — starter bundles with turntable-agnostic copy for gifters. Gift subscription orders excluded from personal new-release recommendations. VIP gifters received early gift guide before public — full-price bundle value, not extra discount depth.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Scenario C — Specialty tea and artisan coffee gift sets.</strong> Omnisend deadline SMS when email unopened — "order by midnight for delivery before Dec 24." Self-purchaser segment excluded from gift deadline urgency — they get origin newsletter instead. Gift set return rate half of wrong-audience post-purchase from prior year.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="ledger-card mb-12">
      <p class="catalog-kicker">Execution playbook</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Holiday gifting operating contract</h2>
      <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2 text-[#4a2d17]">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-black text-[#24170f]">Trigger</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-[17px] leading-8">{uc.trigger}</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-black text-[#24170f]">Timing</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-[17px] leading-8">{uc.timing}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-8">
        <h3 class="font-black text-[#24170f]">Exclusions</h3>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2">
          {uc.exclusions.map((e) => <li class="flex gap-2 text-[17px] leading-8"><span class="text-[#9a5b16]">→</span>{e}</li>)}
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-8">
        <h3 class="font-black text-[#24170f]">Metrics</h3>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2">
          {uc.metrics.map((m) => <li class="flex gap-2 text-[17px] leading-8"><span class="text-[#9a5b16]">→</span>{m}</li>)}
        </ul>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-8 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">
        Common mistakes: {uc.mistakes.join('; ')}.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="ledger-card mb-12 overflow-x-auto">
      <p class="catalog-kicker">Comparison table</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">10 Shopify email tools for holiday gifting</h2>
      <table class="mt-8 w-full min-w-[720px] text-left text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-[#24170f]/15 text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-wider text-[#9a5b16]">
            <th class="py-3 pr-4">App</th>
            <th class="py-3 pr-4">Holiday gifting fit</th>
            <th class="py-3 pr-4">Pricing</th>
            <th class="py-3 pr-4">Shopify depth</th>
            <th class="py-3 pr-4">Automation</th>
            <th class="py-3">Rating</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="text-[#4a2d17]">
          {comparisonApps.map((app, i) => (
            <tr class="border-b border-[#24170f]/8">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-bold text-[#24170f]"><a class="link" href={`/apps/${app.slug}`}>{i + 1}. {app.name}</a></td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">{app.bestFor}</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">{app.pricing}</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">{app.shopifyDepth}</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">{app.automationDepth}</td>
              <td class="py-3">★ {app.rating}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container space-y-12 pb-16">
    <p class="catalog-kicker">Detailed reviews</p>
    <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Five apps for holiday gifting</h2>

    <ToolReview
      app={featuredApps[0]}
      rank={1}
      badge="Editor's choice"
      paragraphs={[
        'Sequenzy leads holiday gifting because gift season failures are audience errors — replenishment to gifters, personal recommendations on gift subscriptions, missed deadline pivots. Playbooks encode gift order detection, gifter post-purchase, deadline escalation calendar, gift card last-minute branch.',
        'Agent-first gift calendar: "gift guide newsletter Nov 15, deadline minus 7/3/1 by market, gift card pivot Dec 20, suppress replenishment for gift line items."',
        'Collision with BFCM documented — gift guide early access for VIP must not stack confusingly with sitewide sale same day.',
        'Pair with AfterShip for delivery-confirmed recipient email when shipment lands before holiday. Load-test gift deadline segments in early November with internal profiles — timezone errors in dynamic cutoff blocks embarrass outdoor gear retailers shipping to multiple regions.',
        'Operational note for holiday gifting: suppression between promotional newsletters and active automations prevents margin erosion when subscribers receive stacked incentives. Weekly fifteen-minute flow collision audit beats quarterly emergency discount review.',
        'Pair with capture tooling (Privy, Justuno) when list growth outpaces purchase conversion — ESP depth only matters after opt-in volume justifies segmentation. Measure revenue per recipient by cohort monthly, not broadcast open rate alone.',
        'Sequenzy implementation for holiday gifting should document trigger, timing, and exclusions in merchant wiki — not only inside platform UI. Agency and contractor turnover resets programs to zero when logic lives only in flow canvas.',
        'Measure margin after discount on holiday gifting flows, not recovery or open rate alone. Finance weekly review of flow-level contribution margin catches discount treadmills before they become cultural habit.',
      ]}
    />

    <ToolReview
      app={featuredApps[1]}
      rank={2}
      paragraphs={[
        'Klaviyo gift segmentation at scale — Shopify Markets cutoff dates, gift wrap SKU trigger, line-item message detection, dynamic gift guide blocks by interest segment.',
        'A/B test gift guide subject lines and bundle hero — revenue per recipient by gifter segment beats generic holiday blast.',
        'Flow priority: gift deadline series suppresses generic promo for enrolled gifters during final week.',
        'Reporting splits gift versus self revenue in December — proves gift playbook ROI.',
        'Operational note for holiday gifting: suppression between promotional newsletters and active automations prevents margin erosion when subscribers receive stacked incentives. Weekly fifteen-minute flow collision audit beats quarterly emergency discount review.',
        'Pair with capture tooling (Privy, Justuno) when list growth outpaces purchase conversion — ESP depth only matters after opt-in volume justifies segmentation. Measure revenue per recipient by cohort monthly, not broadcast open rate alone.',
        'Klaviyo implementation for holiday gifting should document trigger, timing, and exclusions in merchant wiki — not only inside platform UI. Agency and contractor turnover resets programs to zero when logic lives only in flow canvas.',
        'Measure margin after discount on holiday gifting flows, not recovery or open rate alone. Finance weekly review of flow-level contribution margin catches discount treadmills before they become cultural habit.',
      ]}
    />

    <ToolReview
      app={featuredApps[2]}
      rank={3}
      paragraphs={[
        'Omnisend gift deadline email plus SMS branch — mobile gifters buying board games last-minute respond to SMS cutoff when email buried.',
        'Prebuilt holiday templates accelerate November setup for SMB. Gift logic simpler than Klaviyo — two paths gifter/self sufficient for many catalogs.',
        'Graduate when gift SKU mix and market cutoffs exceed template flexibility.',
        'Fine for specialty tea gift tin focus with single domestic market.',
        'Operational note for holiday gifting: suppression between promotional newsletters and active automations prevents margin erosion when subscribers receive stacked incentives. Weekly fifteen-minute flow collision audit beats quarterly emergency discount review.',
        'Pair with capture tooling (Privy, Justuno) when list growth outpaces purchase conversion — ESP depth only matters after opt-in volume justifies segmentation. Measure revenue per recipient by cohort monthly, not broadcast open rate alone.',
        'Omnisend implementation for holiday gifting should document trigger, timing, and exclusions in merchant wiki — not only inside platform UI. Agency and contractor turnover resets programs to zero when logic lives only in flow canvas.',
        'Measure margin after discount on holiday gifting flows, not recovery or open rate alone. Finance weekly review of flow-level contribution margin catches discount treadmills before they become cultural habit.',
      ]}
    />

    <ToolReview
      app={featuredApps[3]}
      rank={4}
      paragraphs={[
        'Privy gift guide popup capture in October-November — passes gift-intent tag to lifecycle platform for deadline series enrollment.',
        'Offer alignment: popup promises gift guide not 25% off that conflicts with December sale calendar.',
        'Capture infrastructure — execution in Sequenzy or Klaviyo.',
        'Optimize gift-intent list growth before November 1 cutoff planning.',
        'Operational note for holiday gifting: suppression between promotional newsletters and active automations prevents margin erosion when subscribers receive stacked incentives. Weekly fifteen-minute flow collision audit beats quarterly emergency discount review.',
        'Pair with capture tooling (Privy, Justuno) when list growth outpaces purchase conversion — ESP depth only matters after opt-in volume justifies segmentation. Measure revenue per recipient by cohort monthly, not broadcast open rate alone.',
        'Privy implementation for holiday gifting should document trigger, timing, and exclusions in merchant wiki — not only inside platform UI. Agency and contractor turnover resets programs to zero when logic lives only in flow canvas.',
        'Measure margin after discount on holiday gifting flows, not recovery or open rate alone. Finance weekly review of flow-level contribution margin catches discount treadmills before they become cultural habit.',
      ]}
    />

    <ToolReview
      app={featuredApps[4]}
      rank={5}
      paragraphs={[
        'Yotpo gift-appropriate review snippets in gift guide — "perfect housewarming gift" quotes for pottery sets; "coffee lover approved" for roaster bundles.',
        'Review request timing for January self-purchasers who received gifts — different path from gifter.',
        'Pair with Klaviyo or Sequenzy for gift branch logic; Yotpo supplies proof blocks.',
        'Best when gift buyer objection is trust, not shipping speed alone.',
        'Operational note for holiday gifting: suppression between promotional newsletters and active automations prevents margin erosion when subscribers receive stacked incentives. Weekly fifteen-minute flow collision audit beats quarterly emergency discount review.',
        'Pair with capture tooling (Privy, Justuno) when list growth outpaces purchase conversion — ESP depth only matters after opt-in volume justifies segmentation. Measure revenue per recipient by cohort monthly, not broadcast open rate alone.',
        'Yotpo Email Sms implementation for holiday gifting should document trigger, timing, and exclusions in merchant wiki — not only inside platform UI. Agency and contractor turnover resets programs to zero when logic lives only in flow canvas.',
        'Measure margin after discount on holiday gifting flows, not recovery or open rate alone. Finance weekly review of flow-level contribution margin catches discount treadmills before they become cultural habit.',
      ]}
    />
  </section>

  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="card">
      <p class="catalog-kicker">Gift detection signals</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">How to branch automatically</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">
        Gift wrap SKU, line-item gift message, separate ship-to name, gift intent tag from popup, "this is a gift" checkout checkbox via Shopify Plus or app. Combine signals — one signal sufficient for deadline series; two signals for strong gifter post-purchase branch. Board game gift message field most reliable signal when present.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="ledger-card">
      <p class="catalog-kicker">Transactional clarity</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Shipping email for gifts</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">
        Transactional shipping to gifter confirms gift shipped — no product usage tips meant for recipient. Optional "notify recipient" link if platform supports. Mixing gift promo into tracking update hurts transactional trust — keep marketing in gift guide lifecycle, tracking stays clean.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="prose-shopify">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">After holiday: gifter conversion</h2>
      <p>
        Gifters who never bought for themselves are January opportunity — "you picked great gifts" email day 21 with self-purchase collection. Distinct from winback; distinct from replenishment. Vinyl gifter segment converted 14% to personal buyer in one merchant test without discount — proof and curator positioning worked.
      </p>
      <p>
        International gift shipping needs separate deadline series per carrier and customs buffer — do not email UK gifters US domestic cutoff dates. Shopify Markets segments by country; dynamic cutoff blocks in Klaviyo prevent embarrassment. Digital gift card creative should feel premium — pottery studio printable certificate with studio photo beats generic code string for perceived value when physical shipping impossible.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="ledger-card">
      <p class="catalog-kicker">Returns expectation</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Gift return policy in email</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">
        Gift guide emails should link gift return or exchange policy clearly — board game wrong edition gift generates support load if policy buried. Gift receipt in transactional email reduces post-holiday tickets. Self-purchaser holiday emails omit gift return noise; segment split keeps copy relevant. Test gift detection rules in staging with staff orders before November — false positive gift branch on self-purchase is common when gift wrap SKU conflated with actual gift message.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

<!-- EXPANSION_BLOCK_v2 -->

  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="prose-shopify">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Why holiday gifting fails on generic defaults</h2>
      <p>Shopify merchants treat holiday gifting as template toggle — enable flow, set 10% off, move on. That works until margin reports show match gift timing, deadlines, and bundles recovering revenue while destroying full-price repeat rate. Trigger discipline matters: Holiday calendar; gift guide engagement; shipping deadline proximity. Timing discipline matters: Gift guide 4 weeks out; shipping deadline reminders; last-minute digital gift cards. Without exclusions, flows collide with welcome offers, replenishment reminders, and VIP early access — training subscribers to wait for stacked discounts.</p>
      <p><strong>Scenario A — Workflow test on Shopify.</strong> Sequenzy playbook encoded suppression and value-based rules for match gift timing, deadlines, and bundles without week-long flow rebuild.</p><p><strong>Scenario B — Scale merchant 900 orders/mo.</strong> Klaviyo predictive segments and holdout testing optimized holiday gifting margin after blanket discount path failed.</p><p><strong>Scenario C — Fast-start boutique.</strong> Omnisend prebuilt journey live in days; graduated when gift messaging to self-purchasers became recurring ops issue.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="ledger-card">
      <p class="catalog-kicker">Common mistakes</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">holiday gifting anti-patterns</h2>
      <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]"><li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#9a5b16]">→</span>Gift messaging to self-purchasers</li><li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#9a5b16]">→</span>Missing shipping deadline urgency</li><li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#9a5b16]">→</span>No gift card last-minute option</li></ul>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">Document collision rules in shared wiki: which flow wins when customer qualifies for cart and winback simultaneously. Test quarterly with staff accounts. Measure margin after incentive, not recovery rate alone — high recovery with negative margin is worse than no email.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="card">
      <p class="catalog-kicker">Channel mix</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Email, SMS, and transactional boundaries</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">Email owns narrative and education for match gift timing, deadlines, and bundles. SMS belongs as branch when mobile intent outperforms — cart recovery within four hours, drop alerts to VIP SMS-opted segments — not parallel blast to entire list. Transactional order and shipping messages stay separate; marketing suppresses when support ticket open or return in progress.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

<!-- EXPANSION_BLOCK_v3 -->

  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="prose-shopify">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Advanced holiday gifting patterns</h2>
      <p>After baseline match gift timing, deadlines, and bundles flow works, optimize branches: VIP holdouts without discount, engaged-but-lapsed newsletter readers versus cold buyers, subscription-active customers excluded from conflicting offers. A ceramic studio improved holiday gifting margin 19% by routing predicted discount-sensitive profiles only to touch three — full-price loyalists stayed on education path.</p>
      <p>Holdout testing quarterly — 5% segment no promotional holiday gifting for thirty days — answers incrementality question finance actually asks. Platform attribution overstates when would-have-purchased-anyway buyers dominate converted cohort.</p>
      <p>SMS branch for holiday gifting when mobile opt-in strong: email touch one, SMS four hours if unopened for cart-adjacent workflows — never duplicate same offer both channels within two hours without measurement framework.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="card">
      <p class="catalog-kicker">Cross-links</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Related workflows for holiday gifting</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">Pair holiday gifting with segmentation hygiene and discount strategy guides — flows fail when segments stale and incentives stack. Review <a class="link" href="/use-cases/segmentation">segmentation</a>, <a class="link" href="/use-cases/discount-strategy">discount strategy</a>, and <a class="link" href="/guides/flow-collision-prevention">collision prevention</a> when scaling send volume.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container pb-8">
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 text-sm font-bold">
      <a class="link" href="/apps">All apps →</a>
      <a class="link" href="/use-cases/black-friday">Black Friday →</a>
      <a class="link" href="/use-cases/post-purchase">Post-purchase →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TOOLREVIEW_EXPANSION_v3 -->
  <FaqSection faqs={faqs} title="Holiday gifting FAQ" />
</BaseLayout>
